    "body": "Even \"switch to std::thread\" and \"add lock annotations\" can very much be issues (an umbrella issue could list the places).\r\n\r\nMy point is that these kind of long-term goals can change. Maybe lock annotations turn out to be more trouble than they're worth. Maybe std::thread would have turned out to have some problematic behavior on some platform. Code comments in general are prone to becoming stale.\r\n(it's not the case, these are fine in retrospect, but an issue allows updating these kind of things without touching the code)\r\n\r\nBut sure, it's possible to think of exceptions, but I think the general rule should be to not add TODOs in the source code.",
